com.arkoisystems.arkoicompiler.stage.syntaxAnalyzer.ast.utils

Enum TypeKind

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<TypeKind>
      • com.arkoisystems.arkoicompiler.stage.syntaxAnalyzer.ast.utils.TypeKind
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<TypeKind>

    public enum TypeKind
extends java.lang.Enum<TypeKind>
    This enum is used to define a TypeKind which is used in TypeSyntaxAST. It is important for later usage in the SemanticAnalyzer because it will check if they can be combined etc.

      • getTypeKind

        public static TypeKind getTypeKind(AbstractToken abstractToken)
        Gets the TypeKind of an AbstractToken through the token content. It will skip the collection type because you can't parse a collection outside the SemanticAnalyzer.
        Parameters:
        abstractToken - the AbstractToken which is used for searching the specific TypeKind.
        Returns:
        null if the method didn't found anything or the TypeKind if it did.

      • getTypeKind

        public static TypeKind getTypeKind(AbstractOperableSemanticAST<?,?> abstractOperableSemanticAST)
        Gets the TypeKind based on the AbstractOperableSemanticAST. It can happen, that a AbstractOperableSemanticAST needs to compute the TypeKind at first like with the AbstractExpressionSemanticAST and IdentifierCallOperableSemanticAST.
        Parameters:
        abstractOperableSemanticAST - the AbstractOperableSemanticAST which is used to find the correct TypeKind.
        Returns:
        null if the AbstractOperableSemanticAST isn't supported or the found TypeKind.

      • combineKinds

        public static TypeKind combineKinds(AbstractOperableSemanticAST<?,?> leftSideOperable,
                                    AbstractOperableSemanticAST<?,?> rightSideOperable)
        Combines two AbstractOperableSemanticAST's and returns just one TypeKind. It is just a sub-method for the real method (combineKinds(TypeKind, TypeKind)) which is used if the TypeKind's of the two AbstractOperableSemanticAST's was found.
        Parameters:
        leftSideOperable - the left AbstractOperableSemanticAST which is used to resolve it's TypeKind.
        rightSideOperable - the right AbstractOperableSemanticAST which is used to resolve it's TypeKind.
        Returns:
        null if the combination isn't supported or the result of the called method (combineKinds(TypeKind, TypeKind)).

      • combineKinds

        private static TypeKind combineKinds(TypeKind leftSideKind,
                                     TypeKind rightSideKind)
        The main method to combine two TypeKind's. If the combination isn't supported, it will throw an error.
        Parameters:
        leftSideKind - the left TypeKind which should be combined with the "rightSideKind".
        rightSideKind - the right TypeKind which should be combined with the "leftSideKind".
        Returns:
        the resolved TypeKind or an error if the combination isn't supported.

      • getTypeKind

        public static TypeKind getTypeKind(AbstractNumberToken.NumberType numberType)
        Gets the TypeKind with help of an AbstractNumberToken.NumberType. For now a Hexadecimal number is getting transformed to an Integer.
        Parameters:
        numberType - the AbstractNumberToken.NumberType which is used to get the specific TypeKind.
        Returns:
        null if the AbstractNumberToken.NumberType isn't supported or is not found.
